Naah, it's not so bad. except your weapons which you prob. already know.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I know what I want to aim for, but I don't know in what order to aim for it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Basically Levels and Weapons are your best friends; and you've got a good foundation to work off of.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You can see what I have and what I want in my magelo link below, if it works.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yuppers. Worked fine.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I know, first off I need to get new weapons.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yep. You got it. <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'm working on my faction right now as I have a Frostbringer head to quest. After that I'm going to take a group to Chef/Bar/Armsman/Frogland/Sebilis a couple times in hope of a RBG, if that doesn't work...my guild can do Tale/Sever/Trak now, so a CoF or CoP might be forseeable.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
My RBG I got at bugs camp <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Seriously. Was quite suprising. <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A new range slot will fall in place whenever I have the 3k to spend, sometime within the next few weeks.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Stick witht he weapons choices first and foremost. Hell, a Goranga Idol is prob the best 100pp you'll spend.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>After that I'm lost. I'd like a Fleshgrinder for my main hand but I know that's a bit far off, can anyone suggest something smaller to shoot for? A guildmember's needing his 8th shawl final fight done, maybe a Snowchipper or the Hammer?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Iffn I were you; i'd do my damndest to just go level up in Seb; save up the shinies; and just go buy new weapons in the bazaar. You're guild is at dragon level for Kunark and their best usage of you is to just be as close to 60 if you're a more than casual guild..Hit them Kunark Dragons for all their worth and get them levels. Sounds to me like you're going Kael Faction so beating up on Arena MoB's really isn't an option...go maybe crash through WW a while on some of the lesser dragons and get some gear there too.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Any particular order I should go in when upgrading the armor? I can get Fierce Heraldic Armor and Earring of the Solstice pieces made for materials, so in what order should I replace them?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Basically whatever you can afford. Bracers are real nice and prob one of the cheapest out of the lot..than arms, than boots/gloves, than legs, helm, BP...whatever your budget allows. Just make sure you don't go dropping your last copper down the shitter and slow down on keeping an income unless you want to be a smith and make the stuff which some peopel ehre have mastered and can steer you in the right direction.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This post was probably hard to follow, but thanks in advance for any help you can offer.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
